body:
To get the number of (SkiaSharp) pixels in a Xamarin.Forms view unit, we are using these methods:

```csharp
// Mac
NSScreen.MainScreen.BackingScaleFactor
// Android
Resources.System.DisplayMetrics.ScaledDensity
// iOS
UIScreen.MainScreen.Scale
// UWP
Windows.Graphics.Display.DisplayInformation.GetForCurrentView().RawPixelsPerViewPixel
```

These seem to work most of the time but not always. In particular the Android doesn't seem to work when the user sets a custom font size in Accessibility settings.

Is this the right type of approach and is there any better approach on Android?
